def labeler(given_list):
    # Classifies Image as 1 = Mask Detected, 0 = Mask not detected
    yLabel = []
    for i in range(len(given_list)):
        if 'Without' in given_list[i]:
            yLabel.append(0)
        else:
            yLabel.append(1)
    return yLabel

In [4]:
def vectorImage(givenList):
    # Reduces size of image to standard size and returns np array to be used for modelling purposes
    all_images = []
    for index in range(0, len(givenList)):
        #img = Image.open(givenList[index]).convert("L")
        img = Image.open(givenList[index])
        img = np.resize(img, (64,64))
        im2arr = np.array(img)
        #im2arr = im2arr.reshape(1,64,64,1)
        all_images.append(im2arr)
    return np.array(all_images)

# Creating Training, Validation, Testing Sets
withMask = [i for i in listMask if 'Without' not in i]
withoutMask = [i for i in listMask if 'Without' in i]

trainXOrig = withMask[:int(len(withMask)*0.6)] + withoutMask[:int(len(withoutMask)*0.6)]
testXOrig = withMask[int(len(withMask)*0.6):int(len(withMask)*0.8)] + withoutMask[int(len(withoutMask)*0.6):int(len(withoutMask)*0.8)]
valXOrig = withMask[int(len(withMask)*0.8):] + withoutMask[int(len(withoutMask)*0.8):]

y_train = np.array([labeler(trainXOrig)])
y_test = np.array([labeler(testXOrig)])
y_val = np.array([labeler(valXOrig)])

X_train = vectorImage(trainXOrig)
X_test = vectorImage(testXOrig)
X_val = vectorImage(valXOrig)

                        MaxPooling2D(),
                        Flatten(),
                        Dense(n, activation = 'relu'),
                        Dense(2, activation='softmax')
    ])
    model.compile(
    optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(),
    loss = 'sparse_categorical_crossentropy', 
    metrics = [tf.keras.metrics.SparseCategoricalAccuracy()] 
    )
    model.fit(X_train2, y_train2, epochs = 30, batch_size = 256, verbose = False) 
    model.evaluate(X_train2, y_train2)
    print(time.time() - start_time)

In [29]:
def plotGraphs(history):
    # Plot the training and validation accuracy with epoch
    plt.plot(history.history['sparse_categorical_accuracy'])
    plt.plot(history.history['val_sparse_categorical_accuracy'])
    plt.title('Accuracy vs. epochs')
    plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.legend(['Training', 'Validation'], loc='upper right')
    plt.show()

    # Plot the training and validation loss

    plt.plot(history.history['loss'])
    plt.plot(history.history['val_loss'])
    plt.title('Loss vs. epochs')
    plt.ylabel('Loss')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.legend(['Training', 'Validation'], loc='upper right')
    plt.show()

In [33]:
for l in [0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 0.5, 0.05]:
    print('Lambda: {}'.format(l))
    start_time = time.time()
    model = Sequential([Conv2D(kernel_size = (1,1), filters = 4, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(64,64,1)), 
                        MaxPooling2D(),
                        Flatten(),

start_time = time.time()
l = 0.01
model = Sequential([Conv2D(kernel_size = (1,1), filters = 4, activation = 'relu', input_shape=(64,64,1)), 
                    MaxPooling2D(),
                    Flatten(),
                    Dense(4096, activation = 'relu', kernel_regularizer = tf.keras.regularizers.l2(l)),
                    Dense(128, activation = 'relu', kernel_regularizer = tf.keras.regularizers.l2(l)),
                    Dense(64, activation = 'relu', kernel_regularizer = tf.keras.regularizers.l2(l)),
                    Dense(2, activation='softmax', kernel_regularizer = tf.keras.regularizers.l2(l))
])
model.compile(
optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(),
loss = 'sparse_categorical_crossentropy', 
metrics = [tf.keras.metrics.SparseCategoricalAccuracy()] 
)
model.load_weights('Best_Model')

model.evaluate(X_train2, y_train2)

model.evaluate(X_val2, y_val2)

model.evaluate(X_test2, y_test2)
